    {
        "content": "<p>From Greg's <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/Z0lG-CIjqvSvKWK4@kroah.com\">Char/Misc/IIO driver changes for 6.13-rc1</a> pull request:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>rust misc driver bindings and other rust changes to make misc drivers actually possible.  I think this is the tipping point, expect to see way more rust drivers going forward now that these bindings are present.  Next merge window hopefully we will have pci and platform drivers working, which will fully enable almost all driver subsystems to start accepting (or at least getting) rust drivers.  This is the end result of a lot of work from a lot of people, congrats to all of them for getting this far, you've proved many of us wrong in the best way possible, working code :)</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 485030335,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1732861945
    },
